<plot>Mark, a 30ish career guy, lost his father a few hours ago. Sitting in the kitchen, tired and sore, he should be taking care of the obituary and other earthly matters - yet his mind wanders in memories. While his wife deals with the situation through distraction and caffeine, Mark is forced to realize: our parents are as fragile as they are glorious.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?110208</url></doc>
